To handle millions of records:

Use B+ Tree indexing for fast lookups
Optimize queries to leverage indexes
Use pagination instead of full scans - Pagination (avoid full scans)


Apply partitioning to reduce data scanned

-> Partitioning (very important at scale)

Split large table into chunks:

By date (2023, 2024)
By user_id (hash/range)

Now query hits only one partition, not entire table.



Use sharding when a single DB can't scale

-> Sharding (when one DB is not enough)

Distribute data across machines:

User-based sharding:

user_id % N

Tradeoff:

Hard joins across shards


Add caching to reduce DB load
Use denormalization & precomputation for heavy reads
